album.title: 2007-07-15: Latitude Festival, Henham Park, Southwold, Suffolk, UK

track.name: Mr. November
comments: Words cannot describe how much I absolutely love this song. [2]
According to wikipedia the song is inspired in part by John Kerrys presidential campaign, hence "Mr. November" since that's the month of the american presidential election.
Words cannot describe how much I absolutely love this song.
"i used to be carried in the arms of cheerleaders" sticks in your head like crazy
I love it how Matt sings before the beat. [2]
the national could charge $500 for tickets and I would go if this song was in the setlist

holy. fuck. this was my favorite song forever and i didn't listen to it for ages. and now it hit me like crazy. i played invisible drums, clapped like i was seeing them live, and hugged myself. it was amazing. [2]
I love it how Matt sings before the beat.

holy. fuck. this was my favorite song forever and i didnt listen to it for ages. and now it hit me like crazy. i played invisible drums, clapped like i was seeing them live, and hugged myself. it was amazing.
Get ready for the play count to boost again.
either i'm reading too much into it or this song is really political.
I'm pretty sure I'd die of happiness if I saw this live.
my steering wheel would be deaf with the amount of times i've yelled along with the chorus while driving
i'll never ever ever get sick of that chorus
